# ===== VERCEL POSTGRES (Recommended) =====
# Get these from: Vercel Dashboard > Storage > Your Database > .env.local tab
# Uncomment and replace with your actual values:
# POSTGRES_URL="postgres://username:password@hostname:port/database?sslmode=require"
# POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL="postgres://username:password@hostname:port/database?sslmode=require&pgbouncer=true&connect_timeout=15"
# POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING="postgres://username:password@hostname:port/database?sslmode=require"

# ===== LOCAL DEVELOPMENT OPTIONS =====

# Option 1: Docker PostgreSQL (Quick Setup)
# Run: docker run --name portfolio-postgres -e POSTGRES_DB=portfolio_grid -e POSTGRES_USER=portfolio -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=password123 -p 5432:5432 -d postgres:15
# Then uncomment:
# POSTGRES_URL="postgresql://portfolio:password123@localhost:5432/portfolio_grid"

# Option 2: Local PostgreSQL Installation
# Install PostgreSQL, create database, then uncomment:
# POSTGRES_URL="postgresql://your_username:your_password@localhost:5432/portfolio_grid"

# Option 3: Alternative format (if above doesn't work)
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://username:password@host:port/database"

# ===== SETUP INSTRUCTIONS =====
# 1. Choose ONE of the options above
# 2. Uncomment the relevant POSTGRES_URL line
# 3. Replace placeholder values with your actual credentials
# 4. Restart your development server: npm run dev
